question: Mickey and his friends spotted fish swimming in the lake. Skip count by 10s to find out how many fishes they saw in total.
As Mickey and Squeaky explored the lake, they noticed ducks swimming together. Skip count by 10s to find out how many ducks they saw.
They saw 10 boats tied along the dock. Skip count by 10s to find out how many boats they passed after seeing 5 groups.
Squeaky the squirrel spotted lily flowers in a section of the lake. Skip count by 10s to find how many lily flowers were there in total.
They spotted birds flying over the water. Skip count by 10s to find how many birds they saw in total.
